svg.text: Flicking of the
administration set
Flicking of the administration set - this can cause damage to the
administration line, and could create movement in cannula leading
to mechanical phlebitis.
Replacement of the
administration set
Force air back
up to into the bag
Disconnect and
purge
Wrapping of a pen or similar object around the line to force air back
up in the bag - again this can cause damage to the administration line.
Disconnect and purge – increased risk infection, loss of therapeutic
dose of the medication being administered, and could create movement
in cannula leading to mechanical phlebitis.
Lorem ipsum
Replacement of the administration set – increased risk of infection,
loss of therapeutic dose of the medication being administered, and
unnecessary cost of additional administration sets (A practise that
is now ceased in cytotoxic administration due to the cost and safety
concerns around cytotoxic exposure).
